  <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Buffering_for_Asynchronous_Signal_Recove_qiu8j35d3.xml" xtrc="title:1;3:10">Buffering for Asynchronous Signal Recovery</title>

  <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Buffering_for_Asynchronous_Signal_Recove_qiu8j35d3.xml" xtrc="body:1;5:9">
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Buffering_for_Asynchronous_Signal_Recove_qiu8j35d3.xml" xtrc="p:1;6:8">Datapath hysteresis buffers allocated in the DCPB/ECPB/OCPB are a major
    contributor to the overall datapath latency. Understanding the system
    interactions that motivate the hysteresis buffer sizing for each type of
    DCPB/ECPB/OCPB connection provides justification for the latency
    contribution of datapath buffers, and how the hysteresis buffer sizing
    might be optimized depending on operational requirements.</p>

    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Buffering_for_Asynchronous_Signal_Recove_qiu8j35d3.xml" xtrc="p:2;13:8">The buffer allocation for asynchronous signals requires particular
    attention to the PLLs involved in the rate recovery of the signal,
    especially if rate transitions must occur cleanly without underflowing or
    overflowing internal buffers. The following sections describe the
    hysteresis buffer allocation applicable to the datapaths segments involved
    in the rate capture and recovery of asynchronous signals. The buffer
    allocation applicable to other types of traffic flow control is discussed
    in <xref href="Storage_and_Flow_Control_Buffering_8iu327oir.xml" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Buffering_for_Asynchronous_Signal_Recove_qiu8j35d3.xml" xtrc="xref:1;20:71" type="topic"><?ditaot gentext?>Storage and Flow Control Buffering</xref>.</p>

    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Buffering_for_Asynchronous_Signal_Recove_qiu8j35d3.xml" xtrc="p:3;22:8">The buffers and PLLs used in the system operations for the rate capture
    and recovery of asynchronous signals are summarized in <xref href="Buffering_for_Asynchronous_Signal_Recove_qiu8j35d3.xml#Buffering_for_Asynchronous_Signal_Recove_qiu8j35d3/Buffer_and_PLLs_involved_in_asynchronous_riu8j35d3" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Buffering_for_Asynchronous_Signal_Recove_qiu8j35d3.xml" xtrc="xref:2;23:231" type="fig"><?ditaot gentext?>Figure 1</xref>
